<%# Locals: state, hand, position, assist, domain, membership, greeting, attention.
    The wrapping node id must stay stable so realtime updates can replace it.

    The state marker rides along with every render (page load and realtime push
    alike) so the embed loader can tell its host page what the widget is showing.
    It is a <meta> because that is inert wherever the widget lands: never
    rendered, and matched by none of the widget's own styling. %>
<meta name="hands-state" content="<%= state %>" data-attention="<%= attention %>">
<%= render "hands/raises/#{state}",
      hand: hand, position: position, assist: assist,
      domain: domain, membership: membership, greeting: greeting %>
